38160926CF2F4B65A8D9CE32F03A2456.description:
Identify personal needs for, and request, relevant technology supports in at least
one personal, social, community participation, or career activity.

914CED9EE40048C18EB147810D6FA6E7.description:
Learn, practice, and analyze at least two learning technologies applied to personal,
social, community participation, or career activities.

64B849260E0D47EB94F0A88DA42857B0.description:
Learn, practice, and compare/contrast at least three learning technologies applied
to personal and/or career development in both current and future settings.

2E619CEC260243BD88A507D124C64F5A.description:
Arrange the most effective learning technologies to facilitate future personal,
social, community participation, or career development.

7EBCD33B69CC4D978D1438F7AF89C9FA.description:
Identify and use information and/or assistive technologies to support personal
management and career activities that are linked to postsecondary learning
success.

958E52D966E04866BEE515A49EC178C5.description:
Identify multiple information and assistive technologies as well as situations in
which these might be beneficial.

606C52D0F446421A8B5188446644E914.description:
Describe times in which information and assistive technologies might be effective
or ineffective in facilitating learning.

E57113737BCF46CD93FC6CC07D637ECD.description:
Experiment with multiple assistive technologies and information technologies
and appraise their overall utility in future learning environments.

6FBAA9A0C26A4821B9091B84BCBD4E71.description:
Evaluate and modify the uses of information and assistive technologies as needed
for future environments.

959D492A424F4AB99B9B56F238382912.description:
Evaluate effectiveness of technology to support and/or supplement
postsecondary learning.

F0FEADA234204C28B39325B0D1C9714E.description:
Identify at least one assistive technology to support and/or supplement secondary
learning.

3BEE6B46ADC5440D8A7B57784414EAE5.description:
Learn and practice at least two assistive technologies to support and/or supplement
secondary learning.

32479386DE694A9CBA6F1D53406DA560.description:
Compare and contrast the assistive technologies learned and identify the ones
most relevant to personal goals.

2F576CC9850142BEB9A54A547CC3362A.description:
Arrange the most effective assistive technologies to facilitate postsecondary
learning in chosen settings and programs.

1C1B5DB484F74421874939474186EEEA.description:
Use assistive technology tools and resources to support and/or supplement
postsecondary learning (e.g., text-to-speech feature, alternative keyboard, voice
recognition software, digital text, books on CD/DVD, mouse, trackball, other
pointing devices, scaled models, tactile materials, manipulatives, videos with
captioning or oral descriptions, Microsoft Accessibility Options such as
StickyKeys, MouseKeys, FilterKeys).

7EDCB940C98944CDA1859E480C649D62.description:
Identify at least two information technologies that support and/or supplement
secondary learning.

9BBEC30693824CE09D4672CF3803DEAB.description:
Learn and practice multiple information technologies to support and/or supplement
secondary learning.

E669EFDC29964FC0B2D5A9F1D0B674A2.description:
Compare the information technologies learned and assess their utility in future
environments.

5E6C6705322148A09D8FF815E424068C.description:
Implement the most effective information technologies to facilitate postsecondary
learning in chosen settings and programs.

B4F10CB576ED4A8F88BBFBAC83CF9510.description:
Recognize and use information technology tools and resources to access, manage,
integrate, create, and share information within the postsecondary learning
environment (e.g., multimedia technology such as Microsoft Powerpoint,
HyperStudio, video, or animation; other digital and word processing tools such
as highlighting, underlining, italicizing, color-coding, large print, tables, shapes,
concept mapping tools/graphic organizers; spreadsheet and graphics programs;
e-mail, texting, iPod or iPhone apps).

2F33AC3E96004714A6270C9AEEDB07DA.description: Identify at least one instance in which technology support would be beneficial.

EB8952C9B2DC42F3938986301992D07E.description:
Describe at least three personally relevant situations in current or future learning
environments in which technology support will be beneficial or essential for
learning.

E60DCE4B7873482BAF0F4E4112B535F9.description:
Categorize the most relevant technology support choices based on analysis of
individual learning needs relevant to future goals.

89C92E3743C1453E92D96C1F4BD4056D.description:
Arrange the most important technology supports for individual postsecondary
learning environments prior to high school graduation.

1ACB85B4DCC24D01BF31BC2BE5A080BD.description: Demonstrate the need for technology support in future learning environments.

9D525CFCE022466F9A9C2DC18EC90F00.description:
Transition Target: Use technology tools and resources to support and/or supplement
postsecondary education or training.

82FF1FCF2E12443987E45736DDAFBA86.description: Identify at least one strategy for obtaining financial assistance.

4E0F21EE1702416286ACBDB5924D82EE.description:
Compare multiple strategies for obtaining financial assistance and identify which
is/are most likely to be successful.

025092D0FCB54D908901DEB27E2BC71E.description:
Complete Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) and/or other fiscal
reporting and application forms with assistance from family members and staff as
needed.

A96C3FB6879A4B96A420EBBEE84058CB.description:
Formulate and implement a plan for seeking needed financial assistance from
multiple sources based on analysis of their positive and negative aspects.

9575653665D745D18440966A014D3A74.description:
Develop strategies for obtaining and maintaining financial assistance (e.g.,
application procedures; prerequisites or competitive tactics such as merit,
community service, leadership or extracurricular activities; and lining up
references).

6E307FFDD5E14EEDBDB51EC558E01932.description:
Identify personal needs for, and at least one source of, financial assistance for a
projected postsecondary learning program.

CBD95F5885454FC7B67BBD7A0D0D35E6.description:
Compare at least three sources of financial assistance relevant to individual
postsecondary learning plans and future financial status.

9C408CAF5B8247E7BA4401A3550CF88B.description: Research and formulate requirements for sources of financial support.

824625155F7B4219A4B5E3A66DDCB205.description:
Develop a matrix with contact information that helps one prioritize the most
likely sources of financial aid and/or income support.

E021F3B3209646EC8DD526CD8D8EFB2A.description:
Identify sources for financial assistance (e.g., grants, scholarships, loans,
waivers, wages, agency allotments, other support agencies).

588194234F32467AB44D93B798749A2D.description:
Identify at least one strategy for enhancing secondary learning that will also
support postsecondary education/training completion (e.g., learning and studying
strategies, organizational strategies, and self-advocacy strategies).

DFDC6317F1D2496DA1DD0704BDCA666A.description:
Acquire and practice at least three strategies to support secondary learning that
will also be useful at the postsecondary level.

03E441A6F58F45B89F4BCD6AE5CEF2A8.description:
Analyze three potential barriers for postsecondary education or training
completion and develop a plan or schedule for the best package of strategies to
address those barriers.

901C183EE625455385C51EE9B914720A.description:
Schedule and implement strategies for postsecondary education/training
completion, monitor success, and revise individualized plan accordingly.

37A2D02E96EF48D2BD3F151309184E25.description:
Develop strategies for postsecondary education or training completion (e.g.,
maintaining and updating disability documentation, learning and study
strategies, organizational skills, and seeking and obtaining support).

09D3EA86132B43FCA774DE2DD1089C71.description:
Identify and request at least one specific need or accommodation for secondary
education.

2A09316C8E184A208075BDBBA95E572A.description:
Describe personal range of needs and accommodations for learning, for at least
three current or future learning environments, and demonstrate self-advocacy
skills appropriate for requesting those supports.

571F93D68FC044269DA4B871D18F0A35.description:
Research and locate three or more sources for support services in future setting(s)
and learning program(s) (e.g., community service groups, student support
services, study programs, academic support programs, and employment services).

536E8ED23AA949F79E07456B168BE101.description:
Advocate for oneself in arranging support or accommodations from one or more
external service agencies (including higher education) under Section 504 and
ADA guidelines.

9C62B8517F42499FAD1585408AFCFCDA.description:
State and appropriately request accommodations and/or other support needs for
postsecondary education or training.

927A1119896245BF91AD5B0A2B6D5526.description:
Compare eligibility requirements for support services during Grades K-12 and
during postsecondary training environments.

A10E691A56EE40599B2CD6BDE3BBC8C8.description:
Identify eligibility criteria and application procedures for at least three
postsecondary support service programs serving students with disabilities.

6B1008C018FD4ADF9142E237CE5E2F76.description:
Confer with staff of one post-school support service program in order to
determine eligibility and next steps.

4361190E1CF54482B825651A655494BD.description:
Complete and submit at least one application for a postsecondary support service
program related to individual post-school goals.

A0D1FE8DA7B74292A0B5085B64174A7C.description:
Transition Target: Obtain adequate, appropriate support services and financial
assistance to facilitate success in postsecondary education or training.

7F0FDF0841764427AC825622906810B5.description:
Identify general components of an application packet for postsecondary education
or training program choice.

0BC19424B58643D585908D7BB18773CD.description:
Complete at least two grade-appropriate prerequisites (e.g., work-based learning
or volunteer experiences, short essay, exam) for later admission to a
postsecondary learning program of choice.

156C8E70C5EF46DE95996EFA91DC8D7D.description:
Complete a mockup of at least one application procedure for postsecondary
education or training.

8E80D3BC35394227B92C23187AC8AA1B.description:
Develop at least one complete application package for the postsecondary learning
program(s) of choice.

FB4E73972A2348D789469540CD3AD283.description:
Demonstrate appropriate program application procedures for personal
postsecondary education or training program choices (e.g., entrance exams
and/or assessments, intake interviews, referral procedures, financial aid
applications).

5B59BFC714914095A0B64A23CF514184.description:
Identify at least one admission application requirement for one or more selected
postsecondary education/training source(s) linked to individual post-school goals.

1617BD39E7AA4F45A909D9A2221938B1.description:
Summarize admission standards of five or more postsecondary education/training
options relevant to individual post-school goals (e.g., high school exit documents,
qualifying entrance scores, courses completed, grade-point average, skills attained).

A9D3FB60BA5F43C58D4EAA4232D3695D.description:
Assess abilities in relation to admissions requirements for selected postsecondary
education or training system(s).

19F7498DCAF547168E11F9550325F479.description:
Demonstrate the academic knowledge and skills required to pursue personal
choice(s) of postsecondary education/training options (e.g., diploma, grade-point
average, specific courses, work-based learning, entrance exam scores).

C40424CE7F424176937E8C721E491D11.description:
Identify application requirements for selected postsecondary education or
training system(s) (e.g., forms, fees, financial aid or funding, selection or
placement assessments, deadlines, community, and/or leadership activity
requirements).

9FEF65AFBD3140FB94E58439D4BAC509.description:
Identify at least one source of postsecondary education or training opportunities,
based on individual post-school goals.

859BB839630240D8AE9B2B72BFFD9EFE.description:
Locate postsecondary education or training information needed to make choices
(e.g., program visits, career fairs, college recruitment expos, visits to colleges and
universities, online research).

0C0EC11FA3D54D388717A3D474E495C1.description:
Analyze five specific postsecondary education or training sources relevant to
individual post-school goals and the positive and negative aspects of each.

A61CBB0AC81646A69A806C61C9AF7817.description:
Choose two sources of postsecondary education or training opportunities and
assess their benefits related to career and life plans.

16478CFF07244B92AA1E617F6D25CE2E.description:
Identify sources for postsecondary education or training opportunities (e.g.,
community education, residential programs, vocational programs, workforce
training programs, apprenticeship programs, and certificate or degree
programs at trade/technical schools, two-year colleges, and four-year colleges
and universities).

60F92765610740C982E1BCE522373663.description:
Identify at least one general area of interest, preference, and/or need related to
postsecondary learning, based on results of academic and transition assessments
and experiences.

B2CC38B9F3774DEFB7F2698D5BBC6E4C.description:
Compare two or more broad potential areas of interest, preference, and/or need
based on results of academic and transition assessments and experiences.

BCFED0F9803746D4A1D44B17D1E1FFB4.description:
Assess and select three specific potential areas of interest, preference, and/or need
within postsecondary education or training, as applied to future career plans.

25FA1257436D42B1A8F65766C37465B7.description:
Choose two postsecondary education or training areas of interest and/or need and
apply these in subsequent decision-making around sources of post-school learning.

2605313FD6E842B09A8CE26AD1570232.description:
Identify postsecondary education or training area(s) of interest, preference,
and/or needs (e.g., arts-skilled, outdoor-skilled, technical-skilled, clerical-skilled
occupations).

745A20D7B9CE4701B1FEFD6B8199BDDB.description: Identify at least one benefit of, or reason for, postsecondary education or training.

C6EA0277B8F14F8E99F1C307CAECDE50.description:
Identify four or more ways in which postsecondary learning affects personal
goals and status (e.g., wider social network and experiences, increased earnings
and opportunities, preparation for career).

42CB219D255547D6A70B18C17E44AE97.description:
Describe how postsecondary education or training impacts future career and life
plans (e.g., skills certifications for work, skills needed to obtain and maintain
employment, home management skills, community participation skills,
recreation/leisure skills and opportunities).

1191E3AFB12D4E5694427A9F0F02DA98.description:
Evaluate the outcomes of at least three different types of postsecondary education
or training related to personal career planning (e.g., skills, certificates or degrees,
career choices, salaries, locations, colleagues).

B5C141D34448464D900A0A9406D05277.description: State purposes of the major postsecondary education and/or training

BBE6EB44BBC34040ACED4ABD7C91B4EB.description:
Transition Target: Formulate and implement a plan to access and succeed in
postsecondary education or training that will help one reach future career and life
goals.
